# ── PRIVACY RINGFENCE — userspace data never ships ──────────────────────────
# Every subfolder of profiles/ is real, private search data. Ship the empty
# folder (via .gitkeep) and nothing else. A pre-commit hook (.githooks/) backs
# this up; see README "Privacy model".
profiles/*
!profiles/.gitkeep

# Generated artefacts — emitted to disk every run, never committed
/index.html
**/dashboard.html
**/dashboard-meta.json

# Transient run files — regenerated every run
_run-urls.json
_run-*.json

# Local Claude Code config (never committed). Claude Code appends runtime-approved
# permissions to .claude/settings.json on every run, so it is kept LOCAL to stop that
# churn (incl. machine-specific paths) from reaching the public repo. Clone-time setup:
# copy .claude/settings.json.example -> .claude/settings.json (see README "Permissions").
# The .example templates and the hook script (.claude/hooks/) ARE committed.
.claude/settings.json
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/web-allowlist.txt

# Scratch / analysis dumps
systemanalysis.txt

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
